    "This problem arises when gradients propagated back through the network diminish exponentially, hindering the effective learning of long-range dependencies.The Long Term short term [30] solution addresses the issue of missing long-term memory of the context.",
    "The network architecture is modified such that the problem of disappearance gradient is explicitly avoided using gates [23] to regulate the flow of information [24] into and out of the memory cell [27], while the training algorithm remains unchanged [63].To avoid this scaling effect, the authors redesigned the unit of a neural network so that its corresponding scaling factor is fixed to one.",
    "This is achieved by the gated cell structure that allows the network to selectively remember or forget information over time.",
    "This architecture has demonstrated improved performance in sentiment analysis tasks compared to simpler word embedding methods such as Word2Vec.,V, to an output, where the query, keys, values and outputs are all vectors.",
    "For multihead \"Attention,\" instead of a single attention function, with d model -dimensional, where the dimensional means the chosen size, k,v,q it is benficial to linearly project on the three values over h times, giving instead, d k, d k and d v, where d is the matrices of the keys and value."
